      • move

        public void move(double forward,
                 double right,
                 double spin)
        move is a function to efficiently set the power values of all 4 drive train motors in one quick line.
        Parameters:
        forward - double: ranges from 1=forward to -1=backward
        right - double: ranges from 1=slide right to -1=slide left
        spin - double: ranges from 1=turn clockwise to -1=turn counterclockwise

      • pushButton

        void pushButton(int button)
        pushButton is a function to move the button pusher servo to press either one of the buttons, or reset its position.
        Parameters:
        button - input -1 for the left button, 1 for the right button, and any other number to reset it back to center

      • pushSoftButton

        void pushSoftButton(int button)
        pushSoftButton is a function to move the button pusher servo to press either one of the buttons, or reset its position. like the name says, it is softer than pushButton and less likely to burn out a servo if left on for long periods of time.
        Parameters:
        button - input -1 for the left button, 1 for the right button, and any other number to reset it back to center

      • resetMotorEncoders

        void resetMotorEncoders()
        resets the encoders of the drive train motors but doesn't put them back to the normal mode

      • setMotorPower

        void setMotorPower(double power)
        sets power of drive train motors to a value, for run to position mode
        Parameters:
        power - power for all motors

      • setMotorTargets

        void setMotorTargets(int forward,
                     int right,
                     int spin)
        sets the target position of all the motors in pulses. probably won't work as expected if less than 2 values are equal to zero
        Parameters:
        forward - pulses in the forward direction
        right - pulses in sliding to the right (or left if negative)
        spin - pulses in spinning clockwise

      • setMyMotorTankTargets

      • setMyMotorTargets

                       int right,
                       int spin)
        sets the target position of all the motors in pulses. probably won't work as expected if less than 2 values are equal to zero adds value of current position
        Parameters:
        forward - pulses in the forward direction
        right - pulses in sliding to the right (or left if negative)
        spin - pulses in spinning clockwise
